yee transactions (i.e., rate changes, reclassifications, etc.). Interviews job applicants and recommends hiring.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>7. Oversees appropriate compliance with all safety and health regulations stated by internal company policy and Federal, State and Local applicable standards.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>8. Implements Company policy of Affirmative Action and Equal Employment Opportunity.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>9. Interprets and implements Company policies, standard practices and security requirements.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>10. Performs other duties and responsibilities as required. Occasionally exposed to disagreeable conditions. May work extended hours or weekends. May travel overnight or on weekends. May work second or third shift.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>IMPORTANT NOTE: This position is located on Red River Army Depot near Texarkana, TX. There is no monetary relocation assistance budgeted for this position. Willingness to relocate one&#39;s self is required and is required to be clearly stated in resume to be considered.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Minimum Education and Experience**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Bachelor&#39;s Degree and 2 years work experience or equivalent experience</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Required Skills and Education**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Required education: High School/GED</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Required experience:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Ability to acquire and maintain U.S. government Common Access Card (CAC)</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Ability to gain access to Red River Army Depot and other Government work sites</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Must have at least ten (10) years of experience in support of Navy C4I systems, USMC C4I systems, or related C4ISR systems development or integration programs</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Must have at least five (5) years of the last eight (8) years of experience with analysis techniques, test and evaluation procedures, or test support requirements for Navy C4I systems, USMC C4I systems, or related C4ISR and C3 systems</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Experience supervising and coordinating work of other technicians</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Preferred Skills and Education**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Preferred Skills and Education:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Bachelor of Science Degree in Electrical/Electronics Engineering, Computer Engineering, Physics, Computer Science, Mathematics or Information Technology</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Prior experience in military vehicle integration for M-ATV, MaxxPro, RG-31, MRAP, HMMWV, or similar</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Familiarity with integration and testing of AN/VRC-92, -103, -104, -110, -114, BFT, VIC, DVE, CVRJ, DUKE, and RWS systems into tactical vehicles</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Process improvement experience</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Familiarity with CMMI and ISO Quality Standards</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**About BAE Systems Intelligence &amp; Security**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>BAE Systems Intelligence &amp; Security, based in McLean, Virginia, designs and delivers advanced defense, intelligence, and security solutions that support the important missions of our customers. Our pride and dedication shows in everything we do-from intelligence analysis, cyber operations and IT expertise to systems development, systems integration, and operations and maintenance services. Knowing that our work enables the U.S. military and government to recognize, manage and defeat threats inspires us to push ourselves and our technologies to new levels. That&#39;s BAE Systems. That&#39;s Inspired Work.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Equal Opportunity Employer/Females/Minorities/Veterans/Disabled/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/Gender Expression. To see Inspired Work in action, visit and follow us on Facebook:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p>